HEADWORD: Scyphophori
<hw>Scy*phoph"o*ri</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
fr. Gr. <grk>sky`fos</grk> a cup + <grk>fe`rein</grk> to bear.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>An order of fresh-water fishes inhabiting
tropical Africa. They have rudimentary electrical organs on each side of
the tail.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scyphus</ent>⟦br⟧
